Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description
Given a string S that represents a URL request. Print five lines contains the following format: "X:Y" where X is the parameter and Y is the parameter's value.

Note:
The parameters of the URL are: username, pwd, profile, role and key.

Input Format
Only one line containing a string S. It consists of uppercase and lowercase English letters, digits, and special characters.

The URL will be in the following format:

[http://www.{word}.{word}/{word}/{word}?username={word}&pwd={word}&profile={word}&role={word}&key={word}](http://www.{word}.{word}/{word}/{word}?username={word}&pwd={word}&profile={word}&role={word}&key={word})

It's guaranteed that all parameters will have a value. The value will always be a string of alphabets and digits.

Output Format
Print 5 lines that contain the answer required above.

Constraints
100 ≤ |S| ≤ 10⁴
where |S| is the length of the string.

Sample Input 1
[http://www.cleartrip.com/signin/service?username=test&pwd=test&profile=developer&role=ELITE&key=manager](http://www.cleartrip.com/signin/service?username=test&pwd=test&profile=developer&role=ELITE&key=manager)

Sample Output 1
username: test
pwd: test
profile: developer
role: ELITE
key: manager

Sample Input 2
[http://www.algozenith.com/signin/service?username=hackNasaUsingHtml&pwd=areYouSerious&profile=ownerOfTwitter&role=fakePromises&key=planToOwnNasa](http://www.algozenith.com/signin/service?username=hackNasaUsingHtml&pwd=areYouSerious&profile=ownerOfTwitter&role=fakePromises&key=planToOwnNasa)

Sample Output 2
username: hackNasaUsingHtml
pwd: areYouSerious
profile: ownerOfTwitter
role: fakePromises
key: planToOwnNasa

Sample Input 3
[http://www.codeforces.com/signin/service?username=Arijit&pwd=jackTheKing&profile=useless&role=newbie&key=wrongAnswerOnTestCase2](http://www.codeforces.com/signin/service?username=Arijit&pwd=jackTheKing&profile=useless&role=newbie&key=wrongAnswerOnTestCase2)

Sample Output 3
username: Arijit
pwd: jackTheKing
profile: useless
role: newbie
key: wrongAnswerOnTestCase2

Note

In each sample input, the provided URL contains the parameters after the '?' symbol in the format parameter=value separated by '&'. The program extracts each parameter and its corresponding value and prints them in the required format.



#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n"   // optional, better to avoid redefining endl

void solve() {
    string s;
    cin>>s;

    //step 1 : find where ? exists after that only url has parameters 
    int idx = s.find('?');

    //step 2 : in a new string store the part of url after ? marrk
    string newstr = s.substr(idx+1);

    //step 3 : create stringstream and new string called part which will store parts/blocks
    stringstream ss(newstr);
    string part;

    //step 4 : loop on ss, and store in part till you get &
    while(getline(ss,part,'&'))
    {
        //get the index where you get =
         int eq = part.find('=');

        //first append substring till = then add : then add substring after =
        cout << part.substr(0, eq)<< ": "<< part.substr(eq + 1)<< endl;
    }
}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t = 1;
    //cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}
